name: Simple GET example with path and query strings
stub:
id: 01-get
tenant: 01-get
description: Simple GET example with path and query strings
conditions:
  method: GET
  url:
    path: /users
    query:
      id: 12
      filter: first_name
response:
  statusCode: 200
  text: |
    {
      "first_name": "John"
    }
  headers:
    Content-Type: application/json

name: Simple POST situation with required request headers
stub:
id: 03-post-with-headers
tenant: 03-post-with-headers
description: Simple POST situation with required request headers
conditions:
  method: POST
  url:
    path: \busers\b
  body:
    - \busername\b
    - \bjohn\b
  headers:
    X-Api-Key: 123abc
    X-Another-Secret: \b72354deg\b
response:
  statusCode: 200
  text: '{"result": true}'
  headers:
    Content-Type: application/json

name: Stub with a few dynamic examples
stub:
id: 15-dynamic
tenant: 15-dynamic
description: Stub with a few dynamic examples
conditions:
  method: POST
  url:
    path: /dynamic
response:
  enableDynamicMode: true
  headers:
    X-UUID: ((uuid))
  text: |
    response_text query parameter: ((query:response_text))
    response_text encoded query parameter: ((query_encoded:response_text))
    Random UUID: ((uuid))
    Host header: ((request_header:Host))
    formval1 posted value: ((form_post:formval1))
    Full request body: ((request_body))
    URL: ((display_url))
    Client IP: ((client_ip))
    UTC now: ((utcnow:yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss))
    Local now: ((localnow:yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss))

name: Stub which uses a reverse proxy
stub:
# A request made to http://httplaceholderhost/todos/1 will for example be sent to https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/todos/1.
id: 16-reverse-proxy
tenant: 16-reverse-proxy
description: Stub which uses a reverse proxy
conditions:
  url:
    path: /todos
response:
  reverseProxy:
    url: https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/todos
    appendPath: true
    appendQuery: true
    replaceRootUrl: true
